    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/234</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 9.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 158</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegraphic
                    instruction No. 28 of August 15, 1922, 5 P.M., and the Legation’s reply,
                    telegram No. 70 of August 17, 1922, 2 P.M., with reference to the boundary
                    dispute between the Republics of Nicaragua and Honduras, I have <pb facs="0567"
                        n="447" xml:id="pg_447"/> the honor to inform the Department that President
                    Gutierrez discussed the matter with President Chamorro and a clause mentioning
                    the boundary question was inserted into the convention.</p>
                <p>President Gutiérrez has instructed the Honduranean Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    to answer the Department’s communication of October 27, 1921, addressed to the
                    Honduranean Minister in Washington accepting the proposition along the lines
                    suggested by the Department.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin E. Morales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
